MTN Group has appointed Dirk Karl to lead group procurement and supply chain management. Karl will take up the position no later than 1 November 2017. Karl joins MTN from Buyln, the procurement joint venture between Deutsche Telekom and Orange, where he was Senior Vice President for Network Technology. Prior to joining Buyln in 2011, Karl was Senior Vice President and Global Head of Strategic Sourcing for Deutsche Telekom. MTN’s appointment comes as the organisation “continues to focus on delivering EBITDA growth in its key markets of Nigeria and South Africa”, it said.